        <prompt>What was significant about Theodore Roosevelt's conservation policies?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">They eliminated all logging</option>
            <option letter="b">They greatly expanded protected federal lands</option>
            <option letter="c">They focused only on urban parks</option>
            <option letter="d">They privatized all public lands</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Roosevelt's conservation policies dramatically expanded protected federal lands, establishing 150 national forests, 51 federal bird reserves, 4 national game preserves, and 5 national parks.</explanation>
